Socket Security: Add VFS, binject, http, webstreams, and ilp sources to node.gyp

This patch integrates Socket Security's source files into the Node.js build system,
plus fast-webstreams deps for js2c embedding.

Source files are split into categories:

1. Core sources (always compiled, no external dependencies):
   - VFS runtime binding: node_vfs.cc
   - Runtime file I/O: file_io_common.c, compression_common.c, binary_format.c, smol_segment_reader.c
   - Runtime cache utilities: file_utils.c, process_exec.c (needed by dlx_cache_common.h for mkdir_recursive and spawn_command)
   - Path utilities: path_utils.c (cross-platform path resolution for binject and SMOL detection)
   - Version embedding: smol_node_version.c (embeds Node.js version in SMOL_NODE_VER section)
   - HTTP performance: http_header_pool.cc, http_fast_response.cc, http_object_pool.cc, response_template.cc,
                       zero_copy_buffer.cc, http_perf_binding.cc, fast_304_response.cc, tcp_optimizations.cc,
                       mimalloc_allocator.cc, iouring_network.cc, http_v8_binding.cc, http_binding.cc
   - SIMD runtime detection: simd.cc (AVX2 detection for optimized code paths)
   - WebStreams acceleration: stream_chunk_pool.cc, fast_readable_stream.cc, webstreams_binding.cc
   - ILP client: ilp_encoder.cc, ilp_transport.cc, ilp_binding.cc (uses socket fallback by default)

2. Optional modules (require external dependencies and build flags):
   - PostgreSQL bindings (node_use_postgres=="true"): postgres_pool.cc, postgres_binding.cc
     Requires libpq-dev/postgresql-devel to be installed. Link with -lpq.
   - io_uring acceleration (node_use_iouring=="true", Linux only): Enables HAVE_IOURING define
     Uses bundled liburing from deps/liburing (upstream pinned in node-smol-builder/upstream/liburing).
     Without this flag, ILP uses standard sockets (works on all platforms).

3. LIEF-dependent sources (only compiled with node_use_lief=="true"):
   - SEA config parsing: smol_config_parser.cc (requires SeaConfig modifications from another patch)
   - binject utilities: smol_config.c, vfs_config.c, vfs_utils.c
   - build-infra: tar_create.c, gzip_compress.c
   - bin-infra: smol_segment.c
   - binject core: binject.c, stub_repack.c, elf_pe_cross_platform.c, remove_signature_lib.c
   - binject native implementations: elf_inject.c, pe_inject.c, macho_inject_lief_wrapper.c
   - binject LIEF C++ implementations: elf_inject_lief.cpp, macho_inject_lief.cpp, pe_inject_lief.cpp, smol_extract_lief.cpp
   - bin-infra LIEF utilities: smol_detect_lief.cpp (stub detection for all formats), stub_smol_repack_lief.cpp

Compression Library Dependencies:
- macOS: libcompression (native Apple Compression framework) for gzip_compress.c and compression_common.c
- Linux/Windows: LZFSE (deps/lzfse/lzfse.gyp:liblzfse) for compression_common.c
- Linux/Windows: libdeflate (deps/libdeflate/libdeflate.gyp:libdeflate) for gzip_compress.c
- CRITICAL: libcompression must be added to ALL targets that link libnode.a on macOS.
  libnode.a contains gzip_compress.o and compression_common.o, so all executables linking libnode.a
  need the library at link time to resolve compression symbols.

Targets modified:
- Main node target: Added core sources (unconditional) + LIEF sources (node_use_lief condition) + libcompression
- cctest target: Added libcompression for libnode.a symbols
- embedtest target: Added libcompression for libnode.a symbols
- node_mksnapshot target: Added libcompression for libnode.a symbols

